The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Healthy rise in Idea net 
                                                                                                               Healthy rise in Idea net 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, Jan. 22: Idea Cellular has reported a 20 per cent rise in net profit for the third quarter ended December 31, 2008.         
	Net profit on a standalone basis stood at Rs 284.01 crore during the quarter against Rs 237.19 crore in the same period last year. Total income increased to Rs 2,606.45 crore from Rs 1,710.3 crore a year ago.         
	On a consolidated basis, net profit of the company during the quarter fell to Rs 219.45 crore from Rs 236.77 crore a year ago.         
	The consolidated results incorporate the companys earnings from Aditya Birla Telecom Limited, a 100 per cent subsidiary that holds the GSM licence for the Bihar circle, a 16 per cent stake in Indus Towers and a 41.09 per cent holding in Spice Communications.        
	Earnings before interest, taxes and depreciation for the 11 service areas rose to Rs 757 crore during the quarter under review from Rs 644.6 crore in the preceding quarter, rising marginally to 29.4 per cent from 28.1 per cent.         
	For the nine-month period ended December 31, Idea posted a consolidated net profit of Rs 526.51 crore, a 31.24 per cent decline over the same period a year ago.                                                                                                                                       
